<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    lang="en"
    xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
    xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
    tal:omit-tag=""
    tal:define="bodyclass string:front">
<tal:wrapper metal:use-macro="main.macros['master']">
<head>
  <title></title>
  <metal:js fill-slot="head_js">
    <script src="https://www.google.com/jsapi?key=${js_api_key}" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">
      google.load('jquery', '1.6.1');
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://code.google.com/apis/gears/gears_init.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://maps.google.com/maps/api/js?sensor=true&amp;v=3"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="${app_url}/static/js/mappp.me.common.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="${app_url}/static/js/mappp.me.new.js"></script>
  </metal:js>
</head>
<body>
  <metal:content fill-slot="inside-header">
    <h2>Location sharing. No apps, no registration, no hassle.</h2>
  </metal:content>
  <metal:content fill-slot="content">
    <ul class="menu">
      <tal:block tal:define="sessions request.existing_sessions or []">
        <li tal:condition="len(sessions)==1">
          <a href="${sessions[0]}" class="button existing-mappp"><span>Existing mappp</span></a>
        </li>
        <tal:block tal:condition="len(sessions)&gt;1">
        <li tal:repeat="session sessions">
          <a href="${app_url}/${session}" class="button existing-mappp"><span>Existing mappp ${repeat.session.number}</span></a>
        </li>
        </tal:block>
      </tal:block>
      <li class="js-only" tal:condition="request.supports_javascript">
        <a class="button" href="new" id="new-session"><span>New mappp</span></a>
      </li>
      <li class="no-js">
        Unfortunately, your device isn't smart enough to start a new mappp.
        It needs to be able to run Javascript.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p tal:condition="not:request.existing_sessions">
       mappp.me is an anonymous location-sharing service. You can quickly
       create a short link to a map of your location and update it whenever
       you like.
    </p>
  </metal:content>
</body>
</tal:wrapper>
</html>
